{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "id": "dm-mutation-10-undo-redo",
  "title": "Undo & redo",
  "root": "b-ur-root",
  "blocks": {
    "b-ur-root": {
      "id": "b-ur-root",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "children": [
        "b-ur-intro-1",
        "b-ur-structure-h-2",
        "b-ur-code-3",
        "b-ur-rule-h-4",
        "b-ur-inverse-5",
        "b-ur-ledger-6",
        "b-ur-redo-7",
        "b-ur-local-8",
        "b-ur-why-h-9",
        "b-ur-why-trust-10",
        "b-ur-why-one-11"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-intro-1": {
      "id": "b-ur-intro-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Undo is part of the algebra, not a feature bolted on: every successful apply returns exact inverse ops, and everything else follows. Two layers share that mechanism — the patch ledger for applied changes, and the editor's local history for typing."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-structure-h-2": {
      "id": "b-ur-structure-h-2",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Structure"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-code-3": {
      "id": "b-ur-code-3",
      "type": "code",
      "props": {
        "annotations": [
          {
            "lines": "2",
            "label": "The change",
            "note": "A shallow props patch, as applied."
          },
          {
            "lines": "5",
            "label": "The exact inverse",
            "note": "Returned by the same apply — the prior value, not a guess. Applying it reverts the change."
          }
        ],
        "language": "json"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "// an applied op and the inverse the apply returned\n{ \"type\": \"updateBlock\", \"blockId\": \"b-x\", \"props\": { \"density\": \"compact\" } }\n\n// inverse\n{ \"type\": \"updateBlock\", \"blockId\": \"b-x\", \"props\": { \"density\": \"normal\" } }"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-rule-h-4": {
      "id": "b-ur-rule-h-4",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The rule"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-inverse-5": {
      "id": "b-ur-inverse-5",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Every apply returns its inverses",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-ur-inverse-s1",
        "b-ur-inverse-s2"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-inverse-s1": {
      "id": "b-ur-inverse-s1",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Exact for the state actually changed — applying them reverts order, props, text, and subtree placement."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-inverse-s2": {
      "id": "b-ur-inverse-s2",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Inverses come from the apply itself, so they are never stale reconstructions."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-ledger-6": {
      "id": "b-ur-ledger-6",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The patch ledger",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-ur-ledger-s1",
        "b-ur-ledger-s2"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-ledger-s1": {
      "id": "b-ur-ledger-s1",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Every applied batch is recorded as a patch with its inverses; "
        },
        {
          "insert": "POST /api/undo",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " reverses a patch by id — document, canvas, and sequence writes alike."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-ledger-s2": {
      "id": "b-ur-ledger-s2",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Any surface can undo any patch: a human undoing an agent's change and an agent undoing its own are the same call."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-redo-7": {
      "id": "b-ur-redo-7",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Redo is undoing the undo",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-ur-redo-s1"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-redo-s1": {
      "id": "b-ur-redo-s1",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "An undo lands as a patch like any other, with inverses of its own — reversing it restores the change. No separate redo machinery exists, because none is needed."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-local-8": {
      "id": "b-ur-local-8",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Keystroke history stays local",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-ur-local-s1",
        "b-ur-local-s2"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-local-s1": {
      "id": "b-ur-local-s1",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The editor keeps its own typing history, with redo, scoped to the session."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-local-s2": {
      "id": "b-ur-local-s2",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "It reaches the ledger only as saved op batches — the ledger never sees half-typed states."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-why-h-9": {
      "id": "b-ur-why-h-9",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Why"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-why-trust-10": {
      "id": "b-ur-why-trust-10",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Inverses make trust cheap",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-ur-why-trust-s1"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-why-trust-s1": {
      "id": "b-ur-why-trust-s1",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "An agent can act boldly when every patch reverses exactly; review becomes cheap because reverting is."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-ur-why-one-11": {
      "id": "b-ur-why-one-11",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "One mechanism for every writer",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-ur-why-one-s1"
      ]
    },
    "b-ur-why-one-s1": {
      "id": "b-ur-why-one-s1",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Human edits and agent edits produce the same kind of patch, so one ledger serves both — no privileged writer."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    }
  }
}
